sentences: Daniel Joseph Donegan (born August 1, 1968) is an American musician who currently serves as the lead and rhythm guitarist/keyboardist for  heavy metal band Disturbed.
In 2005, Washburn Guitars built Donegan his own signature model called the Maya, named after his daughter.
For 2010, Dan built a signature guitar with Schecter guitars, that is based on the ultra classic model (his being the ultra DD).
In 2016, Dan and Orion Guitar Gear teamed up to sell a limited quantity of his custom straps to Disturbed fans.
Schecter Solo-6 2010 limited edition (used in the studio for Asylum)
Randall RM4 preamp with 1 "Clean" and 3 "1086" modules into a RT2/50 Power Amp.
Has used Randall Cyclone and V-Max heads in the past since 2001, when Dan received an endorsement.
Demo Tape (1994)
The Sickness (2000)
Believe (2002)
Ten Thousand Fists (2005)
Indestructible (2008)
Asylum (2010)
The Lost Children (2011)
Immortalized (2015)
Evolution (2018)
Donegan began playing guitar as a teenager and eventually formed a band called Vandal, which was a 1980s-style glam metal band.
Daniel Joseph Donegan (born August 1, 1968) is an American musician who currently serves as the lead and rhythm guitarist/keyboardist for  heavy metal band Disturbed.
Donegan had very long hair during the early days of Brawl and Disturbed.
He is currently signed to Schecter Guitars and uses custom leather guitar straps made by Orion Guitar Gear.
Past:
Gibson Explorer (used in the early days with Brawl)
Ibanez Iceman (used in the early days of Disturbed)
